race.comment: MRS HARRIS (8) resumed with a dominant maiden win at Stawell, starting $1.90 there and coming away to win by three lengths. Didn't beat much on that occasion but looks to have come back better and any extra ground will only suit better. LAFONT (7) is a lightly raced mare who won her maiden well fresh, in a tougher race in town last time. She can bounce back here. FLASHLIGHT (3) continues to race well, second up off a short break here having stuck on well at Echuca last time. He'll want further but this can suit and he draws for every chance. SUBTLE POWER (10) is going okay without winning, good at Pakenham last time. She can push forward and take catching. MOVE THE TORANA (11) is racing well and will be charging late.
